---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const updated = '2026-04-20';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Kefiw"
  description="Kefiw privacy policy. Contextual advertising by default, no personal account, tool inputs stay on your device."
  canonical="/privacy/"
  keywords={['privacy policy', 'kefiw privacy', 'tcf 2.3', 'gpp', 'cmp']}
>
  <article class="container-narrow py-10 prose-tool">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>No account required. We do not know who you are.</li>
      <li>Values you type into tools stay in your browser and are never sent to our servers.</li>
      <li>Ads default to <strong>contextual only</strong> (non-personalised). You may opt in to personalised ads via the privacy anchor at the bottom of every page.</li>
      <li>Health tools (<code>/health/*</code>) remain contextual-only regardless of your choice.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Consent Management Platform (CMP)</h2>
    <p>Kefiw operates a service-specific Consent Management Platform implementing the IAB Europe Transparency &amp; Consent Framework v2.3 and the IAB Global Privacy Platform v1.1. The CMP ID assigned by IAB Europe appears in consent strings emitted by this site; the CMP interface is the privacy anchor fixed to the bottom of every page.</p>
    <p>Machine-readable disclosure of our on-device storage is published at <a href="/device-storage-disclosure.json">/device-storage-disclosure.json</a>.</p>

    <h2>Legal bases for processing</h2>
    <p>Kefiw itself relies on the following legal bases for the limited processing it performs:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Purpose 1 — Store and/or access information on a device:</strong> consent.</li>
      <li><strong>Purpose 9 — Understand audiences through statistics:</strong> legitimate interest (aggregate counters only).</li>
      <li><strong>Special Purpose 1 — Security / fraud prevention:</strong> legitimate interest.</li>
      <li><strong>Special Purpose 3 — Save and communicate privacy choices:</strong> legitimate interest.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>All other TCF purposes (personalised advertising, profiling, cross-device matching, geolocation) are <em>not used</em> by Kefiw. Third-party advertising vendors (principally Google Advertising Products, IAB vendor ID 755) declare their own purposes and legal bases in the Global Vendor List.</p>
    <p>Our full <a href="/privacy/legitimate-interest/">Legitimate Interest Assessment (balancing test)</a> is published separately.</p>

    <h2>Cookies set by Kefiw</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Max age</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>kfw_sid</code></td><td>Anonymous session identifier for aggregate telemetry counts (TCF Purpose 1, 9)</td><td>30 days</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Local storage set by Kefiw</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Key</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>kfw_consent</code></td><td>Your current consent state (<code>pending</code> / <code>ltd</code> / <code>full</code>)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>kfw_region</code></td><td>Cached region classification (EU / UK / US / ROW) from edge IP lookup</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>kfw_context</code></td><td>Session diagnostics context (viewport, route cluster, risk tier)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>kfw-bridge-metrics</code></td><td>Cross-tool numeric bridge values (no user-typed strings)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>kfw-tool-state-*</code></td><td>Per-tool input persistence so you don't lose work on reload. User-typed values in these entries never leave your device.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Analytics</h2>
    <p>Kefiw uses Cloudflare Web Analytics (privacy-first, cookie-less, no cross-site tracking). We may additionally log aggregate impression / fill / click counts for ad slots and basic page-view counters keyed to the anonymous <code>kfw_sid</code> cookie. No user-typed tool values are ever included in telemetry payloads.</p>

    <h2>Advertising</h2>
    <p>Kefiw shows ads from Google AdSense (IAB vendor 755). On pages outside <code>/health/*</code>, if you have enabled the Full privacy protocol, AdSense may serve personalised ads per its own <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener">privacy policy</a>. On <code>/health/*</code> pages and for visitors who have not opted in, AdSense is forced into non-personalised contextual mode via <code>requestNonPersonalizedAds=1</code>.</p>

    <h2>Health tools</h2>
    <p>Tools under <code>/health/*</code> use generic reagent identifiers (Reagent-A, Reagent-B, …) rather than specific compound names. Values you enter are stored in your browser's local storage and never transmitted. These tools are contextual-only for advertising and are not clinical advice.</p>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <p>On-device storage (cookies and localStorage) persists for the max age declared above or until you clear it. Server-side aggregate telemetry is retained for up to 395 days.</p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>You can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Toggle between Contextual-only and Full protocol at any time using the anchor at the bottom of the page.</li>
      <li>Clear all Kefiw storage through your browser's site-data controls.</li>
      <li>Signal Global Privacy Control (GPC); Kefiw honours it as an opt-out of sale/share under US state privacy laws.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy. Material changes are reflected by updating the "Last updated" date above.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Privacy questions: <a href="/contact/">Contact form</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
